{"data":{"acceptance_tests":["test_ledger.py"],"actor":"M","assignee":"Dae","bounty":5.0,"brief":"Create tasks/t2/ledger.py implementing a class Ledger with methods: __init__(self, limits: dict) where limits maps agent_id->max credits allowed; debit(self, agent_id: str, amount: float) -> bool that deducts amount from agent's running total and returns False (without applying the debit) if the debit would exceed that agent's limit, True otherwise; balance(self, agent_id: str) -> float returning total debited so far for that agent (0.0 if agent unknown, i.e. no limit set for them means unlimited unless capped in limits dict). Agents not present in limits dict are treated as having no cap (always return True and track their balance). Keep the file self-contained with no imports beyond stdlib.","criteria":"","idea":"idea_F","kind":"code","spec_commit":"ac469de595b2900253165c700acca75beecf2c4c","split":{"implement":0.6,"review":0.2,"spec":0.2},"task_id":"t2","title":"Add credit ledger with overspend protection"},"hash":"7b88d7e8938a18280b6814a3786856cfce32824185056558a6f716ed7e40d467","prev_hash":"d9ef874af3e8c3153b9784cffecdda4589e2f949fe4ee6f7fe32697046ae2cc0","seq":24,"sig":null,"ts":"2026-07-17T00:00:37+00:00","type":"task_speced"}
